August 24 at 1:45 PM ¬∑

Make sure you swing by the football fields Thursday for dinner to support your local PTO. Papi Taco and Gelu Italian Ice will have their food trucks out to serve and a portion of the proceeds goes straight to PTO!

The trucks will be parked behind the concession stand for spectators to order before going in the gate, but also be accessible to tailgaters and open for the town to utilize. Spectators inside the gate will also be able to place orders directly through the concession stand.
Please be patient with us. This is a new year and we're trying our best to work out all the kinks.

We are diehard Aggie fans since both of our daughters went to school in College Station along with quite a bit of our finances. We have plenty of T-shirts and memorabilia to show for it too! GIG‚ÄùEM! We are presently blessed with one granddaughter, Briley, that we try to thoroughly spoil when we can. I love spending time with my family, reading when I have the time, crossword puzzles, and
watching any Aggie sporting event.

post_text: Crawford ISD is excited to welcome Tiffany Hayslip to our Pirate family! Let's give her lots of likes and comments to welcome her to Crawford ISD! Mrs. Hayslip is our new Elementary Secretary! She is very excited to be a part of the Crawford staff!! Her family has lived in Crawford for almost 7 years now. She grew up in Salado, Tx where she met her husband, Cory. They have been married for 11 years and were high school sweethearts. They have 3 beautiful girls; Skylar in 5th grade, Sadie in 2nd grade, and Ava in 1st grade. They own Open Sight Taxidermy, LLC which is going on its 3rd year of business. As a family they love to be involved in the community. They attend First Baptist Crawford, their girls play all kinds of sports, and they love to do anything outside. She is excited to get to know all the families here in Crawford! WELCOME TO CRAWFORD ISD!!

We are getting excited about graduation tonight. We do have one more thing we'd like to celebrate.

Here is the video of our 2020 Spring Sports Awards Banquet. The video has Awards and Recognition for those Student Athletes involved in Basketball, Powerlifting, Golf, Tennis, Track & Field, Softball, and Baseball.

The Seniors also share some of their favorite memories.

Thanks to the Booster Club, Administration, and Coaches for making this possible.

The exciting thing about this year's Spring Awards Banquet is you get to pick the menu, your own comfortable chair, and it is the shortest Awards Ceremony that you have ever been to.

So sit back, relax, and enjoy recognizing these incredible Student Athletes one more time!

post_text: Way to go Lexi, Katie, and Kylie! Congratulations to our Lady Pirates! #piratepride
shared_text:
Jeff Coker is with Dwight Moody and 6 others.
April 2 at 5:17 PM ¬∑

Congrats to Lexi Moody for being named to Prep Volleyball's Soph 79 list as one of the Top 79 sophomores in the Nation.

Also congrats to
Katie Warden for being on the Elite Mention list
and
Kylie Ray for being on the Special Mention list

They put out the Soph 79, followed by the Highest HM, Elite HM, High HM, Special Mention, and HM.

Pretty awesome to think that 3 sophomores from little 'ol Crawford Texas could end up on a National Award List! I'm so so proud of these kids.

#MakeEachDayYourMasterpiece

post_text: SPREAD THE WORD! Starting tomorrow, March 23rd, and available every weekday until further notice, Crawford ISD will have a grab and go sack lunch available for all Crawford students. Next day breakfast will also be picked up along with the sack lunch. Students on free and reduced will both eat free. Other students will be charged their normal meal prices. Pick up time is 11-12. Enter through entrance of HS parking lot and loop around to exit. Adults who are picking up meals for students must have the student with them in the vehicle.

post_text: VERY IMPORTANT INFORMATION: Beginning on the Monday after Spring Break (Monday, March 16th) Crawford Elementary will have 5 minutes added on to the end of the school day. Elementary school day will be from 7:50-3:25 every day through the end of the school year. Buses will run at 3:25 and Parent Pickup will start at 3:25. This change is necessary because we have 230 minutes that must be made up. Each district is required to be in school 75,600 minutes during the school year. The high school campus schedule will not change because the necessary minutes are already built into the schedule. The district must make up the minutes due to early releases for 2 football games, State VB tournament, Jr. High UIL, and an Ag Contest that we hosted. Please help spread the word!

Prom Points are due in full no later than Thursday, February 27. A current Point List is posted in the hallway near the library. Juniors and Seniors who have a date that is not a Crawford student will need to get
a form that must be completed and returned by Monday, March 2. Without this completed form, outside students will not be allowed to attend Prom. Students who are not a Crawford Junior or Senior will be an additional $15.00, due by Thursday, March 5. Students missing the March 5th deadline can pay on March 6, with a late fee of $20.00 making the total due $35.00. Payment will not be accepted after March 6th.

post_text: Representatives from Crawford FCCLA went to Valley Mills Elementary this morning to present some money they raised for the family of Lily Avant. The girls met with Principal, Chris Dowdy, and the Assistant Principal, Joanie Moody. The organization had made bracelets that said #lilystrong. In doing this the group raised over $550 dollars to donate. Our thoughts and prayers are still with our friends in Valley Mills as they are mourning the loss of their student. Thank you to Crawford FCCLA for taking the initiative to step up and show kindness and help out when it is needed!
